Definition.WordDefinition:
Supervisor \Su`per*vis"or\, n. 1. One who supervises; an overseer; an inspector; a superintendent; as, a supervisor of schools. [1913 Webster]
2. A spectator; a looker-on. [Obs.] --Shak. [1913 Webster]
supervisor n 1: one who supervises or has charge and direction of 2: a program that controls the execution of other programs [syn: {supervisory program}, {executive program}]
